Class Event

java.lang.Object
Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Event>
public class Event extends Object implements Comparable<Event>
The Event class represents a scheduled event with a description, date, and start time. It allows tracking whether an event is complete and provides a way to compare events based on their scheduled start time.

Each event is associated with:
- A text description
- A day of the month (1-31)
- A start time in 24-hour format (hour: 0-23, minute: 0-59)
- A completion status (whether the event is marked as complete)

The class also implements Comparable, allowing events to be compared based on their start time.

  • Constructor Details

    • Event

      public Event(String description, int day, int startHour, int startMin)
      Constructs a new Event object with the specified description, scheduled day, and start time and sets all its instance fields.

      When created an event is by default incomplete.

      Validation Rules: - description must NOT be null or blank.
      - day must be in the range 1-31.
      - startHour must be in the range 0-23 (24-hour format).
      - startMin must be in the range 0-59.

      The start time is automatically stored as a single integer in HHMM format
      (e.g., 1:30 PM → 1330, 7:04 AM → 704).

      Parameters:
      description - A brief text description of this event.
      day - The day of the month this event is scheduled for (1-31).
      startHour - The hour this event starts (0-23, 24-hour format).
      startMin - The minute this event starts (0-59).
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If any parameter is null, blank, or out of range.

    • getStartTimeAsString

      public String getStartTimeAsString()
      Returns a String representation of the start time of this event in the format HH:MM

      Examples:
      - "07:08" if startHour == 7 and startMin == 8
      - "13:30" if startHour == 13 and startMin == 30

      Hint:
      - You can use String.format("%02d", number) to convert number to HH or MM String format.

      Returns:
      a String representation of the start time of this event in the format HH:MM

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object o)
      Determines whether some other object is "equal to" this event.
      Another object o equals this event if:
      - it is instanceof Event and
      - it has the same day, description, and start time.
      Events are equivalent, ignoring completion status, if they have the same description and same start time (start hour and start min) and scheduled at the same day.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Returns:
      true of this event is the same as the object argument, false otherwise.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Event otherEvent)
      Compares this Event with the specified other event for order. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this event's start time is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified event's start time.
      Note that this method compares events scheduled for the same day.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Event>
      Parameters:
      otherEvent - the object to be compared.
      Returns:
      a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as this object is less than, equal to, or greater than the specified other event.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the specified object is null
